             <div class="txtNew" data-packed="true" id="mainPage_WRichText_5" style="top:504px;bottom:;left:8px;right:;width:973px;height:auto;position:absolute;margin-left:calc((100% - 980px) * 0.5)">
              <p class="alignLeft font_8" style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.3em;">
               <span style="font-size:18px;">
                <span style="color:#000000;">
                 <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                  <span class="CSS1Compat">
                   <span class="alignLeft">
                    The NDSG leadership team creates social innovation organizations as infrastructures to empower the sustainable design, implementation and growth of unique solutions to local and global challenges. Over time we have created a mutually symbiotic ecosystem of organizations that can stand alone if need be, but that are focused on leveraging cross-competencies as ideally. We believe that leadership should be diverse and shared whereby everyone in the value chain plays the role they are best suited for whilst having the opportunity to aspire to lead in ways that before were not possible. Overall, we look for gaps in empowered community development and seek to build intelligent means to fill those gaps with compelling social entrepreneurial solutions.
                   </span>
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>

                 <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                  This is most certainly a journey. As the saying goes A journey of a thousand miles begins with one step. With an overall vision of co creating empowerment opportunities with our individual, community and organizational partners, the NDSG team has been working tirelessly (Actually we get very tired sometimes!) since 2001 to build social entrepreneurial responses to community challenges by including all key stakeholders in both the design and implementation. We have always aspired to be generous in time and spirit, humble in approach, empathetic in relationships, and entrepreneurial in execution.
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:18px;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:18px;">
                 <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                  <span class="wixGuard">
                   
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:18px;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:18px;">
                 <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                  Over the course of this journey we are confident that we have gained truly unique expertise and believe the evidence proves this. This has been and continues to be a learning journey. The quote that we love that best demonstrates the value add we bring to the table is this. Knowledge is knowing that a tomato is a fruit, wisdom is knowing not to put it in fruit salad. How does one get from knowledge to wisdom? Experience. Experience and Experience. This has been and continues to be the outcome of our journey.
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>

                 <span style="font-size:16px;">
                  <span style="color:#000000;">
                   <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                    <span class="CSS1Compat">
                     <span class="alignLeft">
                      <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                       <a data-content="http://www.cesolutions.org" data-type="external" href="http://www.cesolutions.org" rel="undefined" target="_blank">
                        CE Solutions
                       </a>
                      </span>
                      , formerly Community Enterprise Solutions and now Community Empowerment Solutions, was founded as a US 501c3 organization in May of 2004. CE Solutions co creates locally-ownedsocial enterprises withaspiring social entrepeneurs. Together we identify, teach, equip, and support impact-focused entrepreneurs who offer villagers the opportunity to access cook stoves, vision solutions, solar energy solutions, water purification buckets, and other high social impact technologies for the first time in their lives. In addition, we now train community groups in how to form their own banks, teach villagers how to design their own technologies, and provide consulting for other local organizations doing important work in communities.
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </span>
                 </span>

OSIIC is led by Ashoka Fellow Greg Van Kirk, co-founder of Community EmpowermentSolutions, and receives strategic and financial support from the International Finance Corporation and Ashoka. Its principal objective is to empower and support entrepreneurs and organizations from Ouanaminthe so that they can more effectively address major challenges within their community. This local network locally implements and adapts proven innovations from other Ashoka Fellows from around the world.

CE Solutions co creates locally-owned&nbsp;social enterprises with&nbsp;aspiring social entrepeneurs. Together we identify, teach, equip, and support impact-focused entrepreneurs who offer villagers the opportunity to access cook stoves, vision solutions, solar energy solutions, water purification buckets, and other high social impact technologies for the first time in their lives. In addition, we now train community groups in how to form their own banks, teach villagers how to design their own technologies, and provide consulting for other local organizations doing important work in communities.<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n","stylesMapId":"CK_EDITOR_PARAGRAPH_STYLES","linkList":["#textLink_itygkgbt"]},"dataItem-ito4rd2f":{"type":"StyledText","id":"dataItem-ito4rd2f","metaData":{"isPreset":false,"schemaVersion":"1.0","isHidden":false},"text":"<p class=\"alignLeft   font_8\"><span class=\"CSS1Compat\"><span class=\"alignLeft\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif; font-size:16px\"><span class=\"CSS1Compat\"><span class=\"alignLeft\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif; font-size:16px\"><a dataquery=\"#textLink_iufj3x9m\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\">SE Corps<\/span><\/a> offers the&nbsp;real world opportunity to&nbsp;work side-by-side with and learn from practicing social entrepreneurs in Latin America.
